page.title: 04Hall Wood,Shenfield
page.content: Hall Wood is in Shenfield near Saint Mary's Church.Local people call it the Bluebell Wood because there are lots of bluebells in it.There are rabbits, squirrels,moles and field mice.Their holes,mole hills and dreys are in plain view.There used to be red squirrels,but now it is all grey squirrels.At night you can see bats. There are over twenty-five different species of birds.At one side there is a meadow and at the other side there is a farmer's field.There is a public footpath leading to it.There are several kinds of indigenous trees.They are hornbeam,birch,oak,ash,beech and hawthorn.There are also several rhododendron bushes.Some local people walk their dogs there.
